						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Bṛihadīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to the 12th century. Except for the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> and the week-day viz., <hi rend="italic">trayōdaśi</hi> and Monday, the other details of date are lost.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of some villages, which were originally made as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna,</hi> as tax-free <hi rend="italic">(iṟaiyili)</hi> along with its income from taxes from the date of the record. All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
